title: Account Creation and Management
summary: Demonstrates account creation using fromEnvironment with automatic funding, account retrieval idempotency, and environment variable configuration.

title: Account Rekeying Operations
summary: Demonstrates how to rekey Algorand accounts to change their authorization address for enhanced security and key rotation.

title: AlgoAmount Usage and Formatting
summary: Demonstrates the AlgoAmount utility for creating, converting, and formatting Algo amounts between microAlgos and Algos.

title: Async Event System for Debugging
summary: Demonstrates using the async event system to register debug handlers and emit events for monitoring and debugging applications.

title: Basic App Creation and Management
summary: Demonstrates basic application creation with approval and clear state programs, including template variable substitution and rekeying during creation.

title: Client Configuration and Network Detection
summary: Demonstrates configuring algod and indexer clients from environment variables, using AlgoNode configs, and detecting network type (LocalNet/TestNet/MainNet).

title: Custom Error Transformers for Transaction Groups
summary: Demonstrates registering custom error transformers to provide meaningful error messages when transactions in atomic groups fail.

title: Indexer Transaction and Account Lookup
summary: Demonstrates how to use the Algorand indexer to look up transactions by ID and accounts by address with proper synchronization.

title: Payment Transactions and Transaction Leases
summary: Demonstrates basic payment transactions with balance verification and the use of transaction leases for idempotency in both string and byte array formats.

title: TEAL Template Variable Substitution
summary: Demonstrates how to use template variable substitution in TEAL code for both integer and byte values, with automatic type conversion based on context.

title: TestNet Dispenser API Client
summary: Demonstrates using the TestNet dispenser API to fund accounts, check limits, and register refunds with proper authentication.

title: ABI Byte Array Conversion Utility
summary: Demonstrates the convertAbiByteArrays utility for converting ABI byte arrays to Uint8Array in various contexts including nested structures.

title: ABI Default Arguments
summary: Demonstrates using ABI methods with default arguments sourced from constants, other methods, global state, and local state.

title: ABI Type Decoding and Struct Handling
summary: Demonstrates decoding ABI types including uints, structs, nested structs, and byte arrays with proper type mapping.

title: Advanced Indexer Search with Pagination
summary: Demonstrates advanced indexer search capabilities including transaction filtering, pagination, and application lookup by creator.

title: Algorand Standard Asset (ASA) Creation and Management
summary: Demonstrates complete ASA lifecycle including creation with full configuration, opt-in/opt-out operations, and bulk asset management.

title: Asset Transfer Error Handling
summary: Demonstrates proper error handling for asset transfer operations including opt-in validation, balance checks, and asset existence verification.

title: Asset Transfers and Clawback
summary: Demonstrates asset transfer operations including standard transfers, balance verification, and clawback functionality for asset recovery.

title: Automated Account Funding
summary: Demonstrates automated account funding with minimum balance handling, funding increments, and dispenser integration for TestNet.

title: Box Storage Management
summary: Demonstrates working with box storage including creating, reading, and decoding box values with ABI types and map structures.

title: Deployment Error Handling and Validation
summary: Demonstrates error handling during app deployment including template variable validation, immutable app updates, and schema break failures.

title: App Client Complete Lifecycle
summary: Demonstrates the complete application client lifecycle including creation, deployment, method calls, state retrieval, and error handling with source maps.

title: App Deployment with Metadata Management
summary: Demonstrates how to create and manage Algorand applications with deployment metadata, including creation, retrieval by name, updates, and deletion tracking.

title: App Factory Pattern and Typed Client
summary: Demonstrates using the app factory pattern for creating and deploying applications with typed client generation and deploy-time parameter handling.

title: Atomic Transaction Groups with App Calls
summary: Demonstrates creating atomic transaction groups combining payments, app calls, and transactions as arguments to ABI methods.

title: Enhanced Error Handling with ARC-56
summary: Demonstrates enhanced error handling using ARC-56 including custom error messages, inner app errors, and error propagation through nested calls.

title: Idempotent App Deployment Strategies
summary: Demonstrates various deployment strategies for Algorand applications including update, replace, append, and fail behaviors with schema break handling.

title: Nested Method Calls and Complex Composition
summary: Demonstrates advanced method composition including methods calling other methods, nested transactions, and multiple layers of method call arguments.
